*help_text clm

*item rdblist climatelist
'These are the available weather files as included in the'
'stated collection. Pick a file to examine its content. The'
'standard collection is in file climatelist as distributed'
'with ESP-r. It is possible to make your own collection by'
'editing the climatelist file and to mark individual files'
'therein as being on- or off-line to ESP-r users.'   
*enditem

*item clm weather_analysis_menu
'This menu allows browsing, editing and analysis of the'
'selected weather file over the defined time period. It'
'also supports data exporting and importing, in the latter'
'case allowing the non-diffuse solar component to be toggled'
'between direct normal and global horizontal as required.'
'It is also possible to extract summary information as'
'required by the climatelist file, which holds the list of'
'weather files to be presented to users. Finally, outputs'
'can be sent to screen or file.'
*enditem

*item clm rad_change_password
'Because of the potential impact of changing the radiation'
'type this feature is password protected. This password is'
'available from your local ESP-r administrator.'
*enditem

*item clm rad_type_toggle
'The non-diffuse component of solar radiation may be direct'
'normal or global horizontal. Given the large potential impact'
'of an incorrect setting, you are advised to confirm the'
'appropriate response with the data supplier. Most native'
'ESP-r weather fles will be direct normal.' 
*enditem

*item clm clm_export_options
'Weather data can be exported to an editable text file in'
'either ESP-r or SQL compatible format. Such files can be edited'
'and are opertaing system independent.'
*enditem

*item clm select_db_opt
'The <select db> option displays a list of available'
'weather files.'
*enditem

*item clm ok_to_clear_data
'Before reading in new weather data you should'
'clear the current data.'
*enditem

*item clmpsychart psychrometric_overview
'Displays a graphical representation of the psychrometric'
'processes of the ambient air.''
*enditem

*item clmpsychart psychrometric_min_max
'The chart focus can be adjusted by specifying the minimum'
'and maximum values for temperature and the maximum value'
'for moisture content.'
*enditem

*item clmpsychart psychrometric_data
'Chart data can be coloured by air temperature or'
'relative humidity.'
*enditem

