'If the ASCII file was exported from the weather'
'module it will have a marker line at the start of'
'each day. If the file does not have these markers'
'then say no. '
*enditem

*item cfiles define_day
'By default, weather collections are annual. You may set'
'start and end days of the year for the data you are'
'importing. If this period is less than a full year,'
'all weather data not covered by this period will be zero'
'in the resulting weather file.'
*enditem

*item cfiles korea_met_conversion
'Different models are available to estimate the diffuse'
'solar energy from the given global solar data. The default'
'model is by Erbs, Klein and Duffie'
*enditem

*item cfiles clm_import_param
'Weather data can be imported from column data files if'
'you supply the name of the file and then select the'
'columns to use for each of the data items (leaving the'
'column index at zero skips the data). You can set the'
 'line to begin reading.'
'  '
'The enter site data asks you for documentation and year'
'and the period prior to importing the hourly data.'
'  '
'Parameter units tare:'
'  diffuse horizontal solar radiation - W/m^2 real or integer '
'    or tenths W/m^2 integer'
'  db T - C real, integer or tenths C integer'
'  direct solar - W/m^2 real or integer or tenths W/m^2
'     integer'
'  global horizontal solar radiation - W/m^2 real, W/m^2 int'
'    or tenths W/m^2 integer, sum of direct+diffuse KJ/m^2 real'
'    or sum of direct+diffuse KJ/m^2 integer. For the latter'
'    two choices you are also asked for the actual longitude'
'    and the longitude difference and to select a method to'
'    use to estimate the diffuse fraction.'
'  wind speed - m/s real, m/s int, tenths m/s int or'
'    knots real or integer
'  wind direction - degrees from north real or integer'
'    or tenths degree from north integer'
'  RH - % real, tenths % integer or a real 0.0-1.0.'
*enditem

*item cfiles confirm_marker_line
'The import file can have a comment line at the start of'
'each day'
*enditem

*item cfiles not_enough_metrics
'For a weather file to be usable, it must contain at least'
'the following parameters: dry bulb temperature, diffuse'
